Defining functions to automate preprocessing task¶

In [11]:
def missing_values_table(data):
    mis_val = data.isnull().sum()
    mis_val_percent= round(100 * data.isnull().sum() / len(data),2)
    miss_df = pd.DataFrame({"Missing Values":mis_val,"% of Total Values":mis_val_percent})
    miss_df=miss_df[miss_df["Missing Values"]!=0]
    
    miss_df=miss_df.sort_values(by="% of Total Values",ascending=False)
    
    # Print some summary information
    print ("our selected dataframe has " , str(data.shape[1]) , " columns.\n"      
            "There are " , str(miss_df.shape[0]) ,
              " columns that have missing values.\n")
    
    print(miss_df.head(20))
    
    if len(miss_df)!= 0 :
        plt.figure(figsize=(20,8),tight_layout=True)
        sns.barplot(data=miss_df,y="% of Total Values",x=miss_df.index)
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
        plt.xlabel('Column Name')
        plt.ylabel('Percentage of NaN values')
        plt.title('Percentage of NaN values in data')
        plt.show()
    else :
        print("This dataframe doesn't have any null values")
    
    
def impute_mode(data, var):
    data[var] = data[var].fillna(data[var].mode()[0])
    return data[var]

def impute_median(data, var):
    data[var] = data[var].fillna(data[var].median())
    return data[var]



def null_value_treatment(data):
    ###
    ### drop columns having missing values more than 60%  & imputing others
    ###
    
    mis_val = data.isnull().sum()
    mis_val_percent= round(100 * data.isnull().sum() / len(data),2)
    miss_df = pd.DataFrame({"Missing Values":mis_val,"% of Total Values":mis_val_percent})
    miss_df=miss_df[miss_df["Missing Values"]!=0]
    miss_df=miss_df.sort_values(by="% of Total Values",ascending=False)
    
    if len(miss_df)!= 0:
        
        drop_cols    =   miss_df.loc[miss_df["% of Total Values"] > 60, :].index
        print("Dropped {0} columns {1}".format(len(drop_cols), drop_cols))
        data.drop(columns = drop_cols, inplace = True, axis = 1)

        num_list    =  data.select_dtypes(include=np.number).columns.tolist()
        cat_list    =  data.select_dtypes(include="object").columns.tolist()

        for var in num_list:
            impute_median(data, var) 

        for var in cat_list: 
            impute_mode(data, var)
    
    else :
        print("This dataframe doesn't require treatment")
        
def if_NA_exists(df):
    return df.isnull().any() # Return True if any of the columns is having NAs

# bureau
'''
Description:
This table consists of all client's previous credit records with financial institutions other than Home Credit Group
which were reported by the the Credit Bureau.
'''
##########################################################################################

# we are creating a dataframe containing five columns which is used to compute first three columns created
c1=df2.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["CREDIT_ACTIVE"].count()
c1.name="Total_credit"

c2=df2[df2["CREDIT_ACTIVE"]=="Active"].groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["CREDIT_ACTIVE"].count()
c2.name = "Active_credit"

c3=df2[df2["CREDIT_ACTIVE"]=="Closed"].groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["CREDIT_ACTIVE"].count()
c3.name = "Close_credit"

ratio_table=pd.concat([c1,c2,c3],axis=1)
ratio_table

ratio_table.replace({np.nan:0},inplace=True)

ratio_table["active_total_ratio"] = ratio_table["Active_credit"] / ratio_table["Total_credit"]
ratio_table["close_total_ratio"] = ratio_table["Close_credit"] / ratio_table["Total_credit"]

##########################

col1= ratio_table["Total_credit"] # Total number of credits taken by applicant with other banks (active and closed)
col1.name = "b_Total_credit"

col2= ratio_table["active_total_ratio"]   # ratio of number of credits still active from other banks to the overall credits taken by applicant
col2.name = "b_Active_credit_ratio"

col3= ratio_table["close_total_ratio"]      # ratio of number of credits still active from other banks to the closed credits taken by applicant
col3.name = "b_close_total_ratio"

col4=df2.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["DAYS_CREDIT"].min()    # How many days before current application did client apply for last Credit 
col4.name = "b_DAYS_CREDIT_min"                          # last because days is in negative

col5=df2.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["DAYS_CREDIT"].max()    # How many days before current application did client apply for first Credit 
col5.name = "b_DAYS_CREDIT_max"                          # first because days is in negative

# out of all the clients previous credits, we are taking the one which has maximum time duration
#left till fulfillment of the credit, its a column with no of days    
col6=df2.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["DAYS_CREDIT_ENDDATE"].max()       
col6.name = "b_DAYS_CREDIT_ENDDATE_max"

col7=df2.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["CNT_CREDIT_PROLONG"].sum()    #How many times was the Credit Bureau credit prolonged(total)
col7.name = "b_CNT_CREDIT_PROLONG_sum"

col8=df2.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["AMT_CREDIT_SUM"].sum()        # total sum of all credits taken by applicant
col8.name = "b_AMT_CREDIT_SUM_sum"

col9=df2.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["AMT_CREDIT_SUM"].max()        # maximum credit taken by applicant of all credits applicant
col9.name = "b_AMT_CREDIT_SUM_max"

col10=df2.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["AMT_CREDIT_SUM_DEBT"].sum()
col10.name = "b_AMT_CREDIT_SUM_DEBT_sum"

col11=df2.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["AMT_CREDIT_SUM_DEBT"].max()

'''
Description:
This table lists out the repayment history of each of the loan that the applicant had with Home Credit Group.
The table contains features like the amount of instalment, how much did the client pay for each instalments, etc.
'''

col23=df5.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["NUM_INSTALMENT_NUMBER"].count()   # No of total installments for all the loan
col23.name = "IP_NUM_INSTALMENT_NUMBER_count"

col24=df5.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["DAYS_INSTALMENT"].max()   # No of days since the last installments, it could be of anyone of the multiple loans taken by client
col24.name = "IP_DAYS_INSTALMENT_max"                        # max because days value is negative

col25=df5.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["DAYS_INSTALMENT"].min()   # No of days since the First installments, it could be of anyone of the multiple loans taken by client
col25.name = "IP_DAYS_INSTALMENT_min"                        # max because days value is negative

col26=df5.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["AMT_INSTALMENT"].sum()    # overall payment done by client for all the loans through installments
col26.name = "IP_AMT_INSTALMENT_sum"

col27=df5.groupby("SK_ID_CURR")["AMT_INSTALMENT"].mean()    # average installments by client for all the loans through installments
col27.name = "IP_AMT_INSTALMENT_avg"

# Domain Knowledge Features  for application train dataset
'''
CREDIT_INCOME_PERCENT: the percentage of the credit amount relative to a client's income
ANNUITY_INCOME_PERCENT: the percentage of the loan annuity relative to a client's income
CREDIT_TERM: the length of the payment in months (since the annuity is the monthly amount due)
DAYS_EMPLOYED_PERCENT: the percentage of the days employed relative to the client's age
'''
col28 = df1['AMT_CREDIT'] / df1['AMT_INCOME_TOTAL']
col28.name = "AT_CREDIT_INCOME_PERCENT"

col29 = df1['AMT_ANNUITY'] / df1['AMT_INCOME_TOTAL']
col29.name = "AT_ANNUITY_INCOME_PERCENT"

col30 = df1['AMT_ANNUITY'] / df1['AMT_CREDIT']
col30.name = "AT_CREDIT_TERM"

col31 = df1['DAYS_EMPLOYED'] / df1['DAYS_BIRTH']
col31.name = "AT_DAYS_EMPLOYED_PERCENT"
